        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 8:44AM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 844 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Candor, or near Owego, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Binghamton, Vestal, Johnson City, Endicott, Kirkwood, Conklin, Maine,
Owego, Nanticoke, and Port Dickinson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
